<p>A student who has experience with selecting from various tools will be able to quickly dismiss those
that are less appropriate for given fractional units. Secondary students are frequently required to
complete calculations involving fractions. Sometimes an estimate is sufficient, so a student who has
a strong sense of fractions could correctly estimate the sum of 115 + 1176 to be approximately equal to 1.
This knowledge could aid in checking an algebraic solution, such as 115x + 16x 17 as being close to 1x.</p>


